{"title": "Androids Are People, Too", "content": "Trunks: What you were doing was cruel, Pan! \n\nPan: What are you talking about? It's just a dumb machine! \n\nTrunks: If he's scared to die, he must value his existence! His life might be different than ours, but if he's struggling to survive, then we have to respect that. What you were doing was cruel, Pan!What are you talking about? It's just a dumb machine!If he's scared to die, he must value his existence! His life might be different than ours, but if he's struggling to survive, then we have to respect that.\n\nAs we all know, Clones Are Expendable, Artificial Humans are abominations against nature, and robots are a crapshoot and undeserving of a second thought. It seems as though artificial lifeforms just can't catch a break in the world of fiction, all because they're Not Even Human. After all, What Measure Is a Non-Human?\n\nA whole lot, in some cases.\n\nIn some stories, you might find that Clones Are People, Too, as are Artificial Humans. And those robots were just misunderstood.\n\nWith the world continuing to shift to being Pro-Artificial Life due to the increasing use of technology in our lives, there's no wonder that this trope is being used more and more in modern works. Take, for example, the evolution of the Terminator series. The first movie showed all A.I. as Killer Robots, while the sequels and spin-offs show that the eponymous Terminators may in fact be people too, at least when not under the control of Sky-Net.\n\nThe Sliding Scale of Robot Intelligence is a big factor here. Nobody's going to treat a 1970's digital watch as a person. If Data is at the other end of that scale, obviously there is a line between the two, but where is it and how blurry is it? On the other hand, A.I.'s might be based on a radically different technology than simple machines, making the line clearer: Isaac Asimov's positronic brains were not computers in any conventional sense (although Asimov himself disliked the idea of treating androids as people, rather than complex tools... aaand then he wrote \"Bicentennial Man,\" where Andrew the robot's status as equal to any human is the whole point).\n\nAny series that uses the term \"humaniform robots\" (or something similar) usually has this trope applying to those specific human-like robots to which that term applies.\n\nThis is related to Clones Are People, Too, and is generally found on the enlightenment side of the Romanticism Versus Enlightenment scale.\n\nSee the related What Measure Is a Non-Human?. See also/compare the Zombie Advocate. Do Androids Dream? is when this trope is called into question.\n\nAlso, this isn't about the Android operating system. That is, unless someone's managed to give smartphones and tablets human-level sentience.", "url": "https://tvtropes.org/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Main/AndroidsArePeopleToo?from=Main.ArtificialAndAlive", "media_links": ["/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ShortCircuit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/DragonBall", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Terminator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/TheTerminator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheNextGeneration", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/TheAsteriskWar", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/AstroBoy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Anime/DragonBallZ", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/LyricalNanoha", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/EdensZero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/LightNovel/SwordArtOnline", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Manga/SDGundamFullColorTheater", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/TheVision", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JackKirby", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/NextWave", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/Ultron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/AstroCity", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/ComicBook/PaperinikNewAdventures", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/JimShooter", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Terminator", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/Alien", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Alien", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Aliens", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AlienResurrection", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/DARYL", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/AIArtificialIntelligence", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/ShortCircuit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Tron", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/WesternAnimation/TronUprising", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Creator/Disney", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Solo", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/Extinction2018", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheTuringOption", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/IRobot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Film/IRobot", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Discworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AlienHunters", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/AlienInASmallTown", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/TheVelveteenRabbit", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/Aeon14", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/QuantumDevilSagaAvatarTuner", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Literature/ATLStoriesfromtheRetrofuture", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/AlmostHuman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TotalRecall2070", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/StarTrek", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekTheNextGeneration", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekVoyager", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/StarTrekDeepSpaceNine", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/RedDwarf", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Neighbours", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Andromeda", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/DoctorWho", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Extant", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/Westworld", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/PersonOfInterest", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/IAmFrankie", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/TheOuterLimits1995", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Series/BlackMirror", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Radio/TheHitchhikersGuideToTheGalaxy", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/HcSvntDracones", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/TabletopGame/Starfinder", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Theatre/PokemonLive", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/BlazBlue", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/DetroitBecomeHuman", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManClassic", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManZero", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManZX", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGame/MegaManLegends", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/Franchise/MassEffect", "/pmwiki/pmwiki.php/VideoGam